    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Access to Taxis</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jean Meyers Ryan letter on Betsy Wade's July 2 column scores lack of taxis accessible to handicapped in New York City (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: Isn't it shameful that other cities have accessible taxis and New York doesn't?</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: Isn't it shameful that other cities have accessible taxis and New York doesn't?</p>
        <p>The Taxis for All Coalition, which consists of disability organizations, is committed to accessible taxis, including accessible cabs to hail and accessible livery vehicles on call. We oppose an exemption for an alternative accessible system that would mimic Access-a-Ride, the current paratransit system, which requires us to call one to four days in advance, usually four days. Who plans life four days in advance?</p>
        <p>JEAN MEYERS RYAN  Brooklyn, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
